The GPS LifePlan is a holistic campus-wide initiative designed to help students plan for their futures. The program provides a framework for students to assess their needs, set goals, and create plans to become more successful in various aspects of their lives.
http://www.gpslifeplan.org/

The GPS LifePlan at Century includes online resources and activities, as well as on campus workshops and events; focusing on five areas of development: Career, Education, Finance, Leadership and Personal.
https://www.century.edu/support-services/academic-advising/gps-lifeplan

To learn more about, view About the GPS LifePlan.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZBh_0NHv0l4
